<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Emphasizes Study of Deng's Theory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Emphasizes Study of Deng's Theory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806134194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1318 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0806134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 8 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President Jiang 
Zemin today called on senior army officers to conscientiously 
study Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics and Deng's ideas on army construction during the 
present new period. 
  At a ceremony promoting 19 senior officers to generals, 
Jiang, who is also chairman of the Central Military Commission, 
emphasized the importance of integrating Deng's theory and ideas 
with practice. 
  He said: "We must pay close attention to the study of modern 
science, technology and expertise, and study strategies and 
tactics of the people's war in high-tech conditions, in order to 
master the capabilities needed to direct modern warfare." 
  The leader stressed that senior officers must study hard, 
unswervingly implement the line and policies of the Chinese 
Communist Party and firmly follow the instructions of the party 
Central Committee and the Central Military Commission. 
  Jiang described a powerful army and strong national defense 
as a "powerful backing" for reforms, opening up to the world and 
the modernization drive, and as a "reliable guarantee" for the 
consolidation of state power, social stability, economic growth 
and a peaceful life. 
  He said that officers and men of the People's Liberation 
Army 
(PLA), China's armed forces, must be vigilant in peace-time and 
be well prepared at all times so as to make even greater 
contributions to China's security, unification, stability and 
unity. 
  He asked senior officers to serve the people wholeheartedly, 
sincerely bring happiness to the people, work hard in the 
interests of the people, and to be honest. 
  The PLA is best known for being well-organized and strictly 
observing discipline, said Jiang, general secretary of the party 
Central Committee. 
  For this reason, senior officers must set an example in 
observing discipline and implementing rules and regulations, he 
said. 
  They must also implement to the letter the decisions, orders 
and directives of the party Central Committee and the Central 
Military Commission, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

