<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Governor Meets With Visiting Mainland Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Governor Meets With Visiting Mainland Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0906050994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0428 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0906050994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, June 9 (XINHUA) -- Macao Governor General 
Vasco Joaquim Rocha Vieira met here this morning a visiting 
delegation of members of the former Macao Basic Law Drafting 
Committee from China's mainland. 
  Chen Ziying, deputy director of the Hong Kong and Macao 
Affairs Office of the State Council, told this reporter after 
meeting that both sides expressed their satisfaction on the 
friendly cooperation between the two governments of China and 
Portugal over Macao issue. He added, the two sides were also 
optimistic about the development and future of Macao. 
  At the invitation of the Association for Promotion of the 
Macao Basic Law, the delegation arrived in Macao on June 6. 
During their stay in Macao, they attended a symposium on the 
role of the Macao Basic Law in safeguarding the economic 
development in Macao and visited Macao Airport project and 
several large scale infrastructure projects here. 
  The delegation will leave Macao for Beijing this afternoon. 

</TEXT>

