<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Debt Issue Agreement on New Airport Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Debt Issue Agreement on New Airport Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806143594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1401 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0806143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, June 8 (XINHUA) -- A signing ceremony on a 
1.2 billion Hong Kong dollar (155 million U.S. dollars) debt 
issuing was held here today between the Macao Airport Franchise 
Company and China Development Finance Company (Hong Kong) Ltd. 
  According to the agreement, the 155 million U.S. dollars 
debt 
will be raised through bond-issuing in Hong Kong, with the China 
Development Finance Company as its arranger and lead manager. 
The Macao Airport Franchise Company is the borrower and the 
Bank of China Macao branch provides unconditional guarantee. 
Half of the bonds with fixed interest rate will expires in 2001 
and the other half with floating interest rate will be expires 
in the year 2002. 
  So far, the Macao airport construction financing Structure 
is 
as follows: three billion patacas in equity, 3.2 billion in 
bank loans and 1.1 billion in development gains. The total 
investment to the airport project will be 7.3 billion Macao 
patacas (912.5 million U.S. dollars). 
  The Macao international airport of the Taipa Island is 
scheduled to be in trial use in next July and to become fully 
operational in January of 1996. 

</TEXT>

