<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daughter Insists Deng Still in `Good Shape' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daughter Insists Deng Still in `Good Shape' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0906053494 Hong Kong AFP in English 0459 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0906053494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 9 (AFP)--Chinese paramount leader 
Deng Xiaoping -- who turns 90 in August -- is in good shape, his 
daughter, Deng Rong, was quoted Thursday as saying. "My father 
is not suffering from any illness and is in good shape," she 
said Wednesday during a visit to a charity, the Hope Project, 
which helps educate children in poor regions. 
  The report in the YOUTH DAILY added that Deng Rong gave the 
charity 15,000 yuan (1,700 dollars) -- the sum she recently won 
in a court judgement against a publisher accused of illegally 
printing copies of her biography of her father. 
  Deng Xiaoping has not been seen in public since February, 
when television pictures showed him at a Lunar New Year 
ceremony. He seemed in physical decline, with dull eyes and a 
shuffling gait. 

</TEXT>

