seem fit for Peruvian conditions. 
  Both fujimori and Zhu agreed that a still greater potential 
is yet to be developed in the civil aviation industry and other 
economic sectors. 
  An agreement was recently signed between CATIC and the 
relevant Peruvian department on CATIC providing 31 million U.S. 
dollars worth of road-building machinery to Peru develop its 
infrastructure construction. 

