<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 12 KYODO -- Chinese Foreign Minister 
Qian Qichen told visiting Japanese Foreign Minister Koji 
Kakizawa on Sunday [12 June] Beijing doubts the effectiveness of 
economic sanctions planned for North Korea over its suspected 
nuclear arms development, Japanese officials said. 
  Qian made the comment during a meeting with Kakizawa, who 
arrived from Seoul earlier in the day after talks with South 
Korean leaders. 
  Kakizawa told Qian China's positive commitment is important 
in the debate over what response the international community 
takes through the United Nations Security Council to North 
Korea's rejection of unimpeded access to its nuclear facilities, 
the officials said. 

