<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing Receives DPRK's Choe Kwang, Urges `Dialogue' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liu Huaqing Receives DPRK's Choe Kwang, Urges `Dialogue' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1306075094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0732 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1306075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 13 (XINHUA) -- Liu Huaqing, 
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission, said here 
today that the parties concerned should try every means to 
resort to dialogue for settling the nuclear issue on the Korean 
peninsula. 
  During a meeting with Choe Kwang, chief of the General Staff 
of the Korean People's Army, and his party this morning at the 
Diaoyutai State Guesthouse, Liu said that on the Korean 
peninsula nuclear issue, it is China's basic goal to promote 
denuclearization and maintain peace and stability in the region. 
  The people and armies of China and the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea (DPRK) enjoyed profound friendship, Liu said, 
and such valuable friendship should be passed on from generation 
to generation. 
  He said he believed that the delegation's current visit to 
China would be helpful to promoting mutual understanding and 
friendship. 
  Choe, expressing his happiness to meet Liu again five years 
after their first meeting during Liu's DPRK visit, said he 
appreciated China's effort in developing friendship between DPRK 
and China. 
  During the meeting, both army leaders expressed the hope 
that 
there would be more military exchanges between the two armies. 
  Besides Beijing, the delegation, which arrived here on June 
6 
at the invitation of Zhang Wannian, chief of the General Staff 
of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, has visited Shanghai 
and Hangzhou. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

